This paper is about non-autoregressive translation models, which are commonly studied in the natural language processing (NLP) community. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper proposes two novel methods to address the multimodality problem, which involves predicting neighbor tokens and attending the whole vocabulary for each position. These methods involve machine learning techniques such as attention mechanisms and may fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions a dynamic bidirectional decoding approach, which may involve neural networks and optimization techniques, and could be relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed model on four benchmarks, which may involve computer vision techniques for image captioning, and could be relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
